snippet.textDisplay:
I really dislike people who act so shocked or angry at how crazy or silly these movies go with their set pieces and action. Like, come on?! The Fast and Furious movies have been over-the-top since like 4-5. Heck, even the first 3 were cheezy, silly action movies... Just with slightly less crazy. These movies are blockbuster action movies, they are not made to be realistic or accurate or even down to earth... They are made to be wacky and crazy. They are made to be enjoyed and just have a good time with... No deep plot, no heavy thinking... Just sit back and enjoy the mayhem that appears on screen with a cast of loveable and silly characters. I think some people take movies too seriously sometimes... They forget the first reason movies exist, 'to entertain'.

If this kind of movie isn't someone's thing, that's fine. But to the people to criticize or complain about all the stuff that happens like they expected Citizen Kane, then just stop...Please.

My theory on how Han survived.....
Han survived just like Letty did when her car exploded I mean she lost her memory but Han got lucky and was able to recover from his injuries without any problem. Now the main question arrives why Dom didn't knew Han is alive? well just like he didn't knew Letty was alive I think when the car was about to explode he somehow managed to get out of the car. The kid Shawn and his girlfriend thought it's better to leave before the cops arrive so they left and didn't saw Han getting out of the car. Takahashi also left shortly after he saw the car blew. Han got treated in some XYZ hospital and since the person who brought Han to the hospital didn't knew his name he was treated as an anonymous patient and when he got out of the hospital the first thing he did was he got in touch with the crew and Letty was the first one to know about it according to the trailer. (That scene is a Easter egg because Letty has also been in a similar car crash where the car exploded and she survived) 😎
